{
  "name": "getContact",
  "description": "Returns a Contact instance for a given contact id. Deleted contacts can be still retrieved but will be marked as deleted. Deleted contacts will not be shown in search request.",
  "parameters": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "id": {
        "format": "int64",
        "type": "integer",
        "description": "An id of a contact"
      },
      "fields": {
        "type": "string",
        "description": "Limit fields received in response. E.g. fields: id, name or fields items (id, name), see more at [partial response](https://developers.callfire.com/docs.html#partial-response) page."
      }
    },
    "required": [
      "id"
    ]
  },
  "handler": "http",
  "request": {
    "method": "GET",
    "url": {
      "$uri": "https://api.callfire.com/v2/contacts/{id}{?fields}"
    }
  },
  "responses": {
    "200": {
      "$encode": "markdown",
      "$block": [
        {
          "$h1": "Object"
        },
        "Represents a contact in CallFire platform. Contains info about the people you want to contact. It allows you to store a user-defined properties for each contact",
        "**Key properties:**",
        {
          "$ul": [
            "**deleted**: A deleted contact, deleted contacts are hidden from search results",
            "**externalId**: An external id of a contact for syncing with external sources",
            "**externalSystem**: External system that external id refers to",
            "**extraPhone1**: Phone number in E.164 format (11-digit). Example: 12132000384",
            "**extraPhone2**: Phone number in E.164 format (11-digit). Example: 12132000384",
            "**extraPhone3**: Phone number in E.164 format (11-digit). Example: 12132000384",
            "**firstName**: A first name of a contact",
            "**homePhone**: Phone number in E.164 format (11-digit). Example: 12132000384",
            "**id**: An id of a contact",
            "**lastName**: A last name of a contact",
            "**mobilePhone**: Phone number in E.164 format (11-digit). Example: 12132000384",
            "**properties**: Map of user-defined string properties for contact",
            "**workPhone**: Phone number in E.164 format (11-digit). Example: 12132000384",
            "**zipcode**: A Zip code of a contact"
          ]
        },
        {
          "$lang": "json",
          "$code": {
            "$encode": "json",
            "$indent": true,
            "$content": {
              "$": "$.body"
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
